narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A good class to learn about cultural, racial, and gender identity, in both the context of a family and in a broader scale.
I would recommend this course for students interested in a good overview of the concepts of gender, culture and identity

A really good course about WGSS. A ton of readings, but a vast majority is very interesting. Definitely do the readings, though, because she will call on you if you haven't spoken in class. A good class to take if you like discussions. The content in very South Asian heavy, so for someone looking for a more East Asian slant (like I was), this will not be that.
I wouldn't. It's a twice a week lecture that barely has enough to talk about in each class. With some better organization, it could be better.

A great course on how family, gender roles, societal norms and culture all intersect, especially in the context of U.S. and Asian households. It is a great course with very interesting readings and film assignments. I always enjoy the reading and the films.
